payload.philosophy: TypeScript should be written as pure functional code, following Haskell principles
payload.rationale: Revolutionary projects require revolutionary approaches. Conventional OOP/imperative style creates technical debt.
payload.conventional_approach: Classes, interfaces, mutations, loops, multi-parameter functions
payload.revolutionary_approach: Pure functions, type aliases, immutability, recursion/HOFs, curried functions
benefits: Composability - functions compose like mathematical functions
Testability - pure functions are trivial to test
Reasoning - no hidden state or side effects
Debugging - data flow is explicit and traceable
